                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.51/3698: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany (<persName type="to">Dodd</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-18T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 18, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. My 123, October 9, 5 p.m. The Department wishes to determine whether formal
                    protest based on Article VII of Treaty of Friendship, Commerce and Consular
                        Rights<note n="94" xml:id="d314fn94">Between the United States and Germany,
                        signed at Washington, December 8. 1923, <ref target="frus1923v02#pg_29">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1923, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 29</ref>.</note> is warranted by
                    preferential treatment granted Swiss bondholders. Please telegraph fully and
                    give your recommendations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
